<bug no-bug="" comments="">
    <id>618</id>
    <title ob="" eb="x" sr="">Transactions shouldn't be deleted if there's some error when exporting</title>
    <desc>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="1.1">#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="1.2">Export with:</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="1.3">- format: QIF or OFX</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="1.4">- target: DropBox, Google Drive or ownCloud</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="x" id="1.5">- check Delete transactions after export option</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="2">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="2.1">#### Expected behaviour</st>
            <st ob="x" eb="" sr="" id="2.2">If there's an error exporting the file to the selected target, no transactions are deleted.</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="3">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="3.1">#### Actual behaviour</st>
            <st ob="x" eb="" sr="" id="3.2">Transactions are deleted even when the file hasn't made to the target.</st>
        </parg>
        <parg ob="" eb="" sr="" id="4">
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="4.1">#### Software specifications</st>
            <st ob="" eb="" sr="" id="4.2">* GnuCash Android version: 2.1.3</st>
        </parg>
    </desc>
</bug>
